problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/subtree-of-another-tree/description/
Intuition
The problem asks us to determine whether subroot exsists as a subtree of root.

we can break the problem into two simpler taks.

compare two trees to check if they are exactly identical.
search every node in main tree and at each node check whether the subtree rooted there is identical to subroot.
to compare two trees we reuse the recursive approach from lc100 same tree , if the current node does not match subroot we recursively continue , searching in the left and right subtrees , if any subtree matches we return True.

Complexity
Time complexity:
Let:
N = Number of nodes in root
M = Number of nodes in subRoot
Time Complexity
In the worst case, we attempt to match subRoot starting from every node in root.
Each call to sameTree() may compare up to M nodes.
Time Complexity: O(N × M)

Space complexity:
Space Complexity
The recursive search (isSubtree) can go as deep as the height of root.
The recursive comparison (sameTree) can go as deep as the height of subRoot.
These recursive calls are not nested indefinitely; at any moment, the maximum recursion stack is proportional to the combined heights of the trees.
Space Complexity: O(H₁ + H₂)

where:

H₁ = height of root
H₂ = height of subRoot

In the worst case of completely skewed trees:

Space Complexity: O(N + M)

In balanced trees:

Space Complexity: O(log N + log M)

Code
# Definition for a binary tree node.
# class TreeNode:
#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):
#         self.val = val
#         self.left = left
#         self.right = right
class Solution:
    def isSubtree(self, root: Optional[TreeNode], subRoot: Optional[TreeNode]) -> bool:
        def sameTree(root1,root2):
            if root1 is None and root2 is None:
                return True
            if root1 is None or root2 is None:
                return False
            if root1.val != root2.val: return False
            r1 = sameTree(root1.left,root2.left)
            r2 = sameTree(root1.right,root2.right)
            return r1 and r2
        if root is None:return False
        if sameTree(root,subRoot): return True
        return self.isSubtree(root.left,subRoot) or self.isSubtree(root.right,subRoot)
